records.addlTxt:
Defendant Mitchell T Picord in court with attorney Eric Richard Hart.  
Patricia I. Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, Consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 3 days. 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*9 months in the House of Correction, straight time- STAYED for agent use to address probation violations;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens- agent to impose 10 days straight time for any/each positive test;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community  (no place where drugs are possessed, used, or sold)- any violation shall result in condition time in HOC: 1st violation- 10 days, 2nd- 25 days, 3rd- 40 days, 4th- balance of condition time to be served.  Upon 4th violation the court recommends revocation;
*No contact with co-actor Jacob O. Leszczynski;
*Participate in Cognitive Behavior Therapy program;
*Perform 25 hours of community service speaking to youth/churches regarding drug experience and death of friend;
*Draft and turn over to agent within 45 days a memorandum clearly and truthfully describing this incident- failure to do so shall result in lift of stay as to 9 months condition time;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment;
*Seek vocational and/or educational training;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

Appeal rights given by the Court. 
Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
